1
00:00:30,018 --> 00:00:31,520
<i>This is crazy.</i>

2
00:00:31,603 --> 00:00:34,565
<i>But it was so good.</i>

3
00:00:37,192 --> 00:00:39,069
I want to keep sleeping like this.

4
00:00:39,653 --> 00:00:40,696
Me too.

5
00:00:42,531 --> 00:00:44,074
Should we skip school?

6
00:01:28,577 --> 00:01:31,538
<i>At least if I was drunk,
I could have used that as an excuse.</i>

7
00:01:36,668 --> 00:01:41,340
EPISODE 4: I KNOW IT ISN'T LOVE.
NEVERTHELESS,

8
00:01:48,764 --> 00:01:51,224
-Are you okay?
-Yes.

9
00:01:51,308 --> 00:01:53,602
Where's the hair dryer?

10
00:01:54,186 --> 00:01:56,480
-Darn it.
-Let's talk.

11
00:01:58,315 --> 00:02:00,484
Hey, put your clothes on!

12
00:02:04,196 --> 00:02:06,740
I must have alcohol-related dementia.

13
00:02:07,240 --> 00:02:09,743
I don't remember what happened yesterday.

14
00:02:10,285 --> 00:02:12,412
-So--
-It was a mistake?

15
00:02:12,496 --> 00:02:13,622
What?

16
00:02:17,834 --> 00:02:21,296
Yes. Honestly, we both
made a mistake while drunk, right?

17
00:02:22,422 --> 00:02:25,217
So there's nothing to change between us.

18
00:02:26,051 --> 00:02:27,135
Don't you think?

19
00:02:27,636 --> 00:02:28,720
I'm leaving.

20
00:02:29,304 --> 00:02:32,516
Hey! Wait!

21
00:02:37,229 --> 00:02:40,148
Darn it! I must have lost my mind!

22
00:02:40,899 --> 00:02:43,193
Why did it have to be him?

23
00:02:53,203 --> 00:02:54,454
Is that mine?

24
00:02:55,247 --> 00:02:58,041
Yes. I washed it.

25
00:02:59,751 --> 00:03:01,086
It's fine, you can have it.

26
00:03:02,295 --> 00:03:03,839
Or just throw it away.

27
00:03:04,840 --> 00:03:07,342
Right.
I'm going to have breakfast outside.

28
00:03:08,009 --> 00:03:09,177
Outside?

29
00:03:09,261 --> 00:03:10,470
By myself.

30
00:03:11,638 --> 00:03:14,850
Oh, right. I get it.

31
00:03:15,517 --> 00:03:17,561
I should get some more sleep.

32
00:03:18,228 --> 00:03:19,479
Go ahead.

33
00:03:24,192 --> 00:03:25,777
I want to keep seeing you.

34
00:03:27,821 --> 00:03:28,697
What about you?

35
00:03:29,281 --> 00:03:30,907
<i>This is it.</i>

36
00:03:30,991 --> 00:03:32,284
What do you mean?

37
00:03:32,367 --> 00:03:33,660
Should we meet up sometimes?

38
00:03:34,244 --> 00:03:37,247
<i>So he's asking if I want to meet up</i>

39
00:03:37,873 --> 00:03:40,917
<i>and sleep with him sometimes</i>

40
00:03:41,001 --> 00:03:42,669
<i>without dating?</i>

41
00:03:43,628 --> 00:03:44,963
I'm not sure.

42
00:03:46,173 --> 00:03:47,507
Think about it and tell me.

43
00:03:48,216 --> 00:03:52,179
I'll be off. Go to the hospital
if you're not feeling well. Okay?

44
00:03:53,054 --> 00:03:54,264
Okay.

45
00:04:18,997 --> 00:04:20,290
Park Jae-eon?

46
00:04:36,723 --> 00:04:39,684
-It wasn't a mistake for me.
-What?

47
00:04:39,768 --> 00:04:42,938
And things won't be the same
for me, either.

48
00:04:43,021 --> 00:04:45,774
So I don't think I can pretend
it didn't happen.

49
00:04:51,738 --> 00:04:53,073
What if you don't?

50
00:04:53,156 --> 00:04:57,035
I don't think I can stay friends
with you now.

51
00:04:57,118 --> 00:04:58,495
Then what?

52
00:05:00,539 --> 00:05:02,916
-You don't mean…
-Be my girlfriend.

53
00:05:09,256 --> 00:05:12,300
Hey! You…

54
00:05:14,261 --> 00:05:18,682
You want to date because we slept
together once? You're overreacting.

55
00:05:18,765 --> 00:05:19,975
Do you like me?

56
00:05:23,645 --> 00:05:26,189
See? You can't answer that.

57
00:05:26,273 --> 00:05:29,693
Plus, I really don't want to date
within such a small department.

58
00:05:29,776 --> 00:05:31,236
Rumors will spread so quickly.

59
00:05:31,319 --> 00:05:32,988
It's going to be really irritating.

60
00:05:37,617 --> 00:05:38,702
All right.

61
00:05:39,828 --> 00:05:43,164
I understand how you feel,
so I'll take care of my own feelings.

62
00:05:43,748 --> 00:05:47,085
What do you mean? Hey!

63
00:05:51,506 --> 00:05:54,384
The guy Sol brought over last night.
Was he her boyfriend?

64
00:05:55,468 --> 00:05:56,553
I don't know.

65
00:05:57,429 --> 00:05:59,514
Jeez!

66
00:06:00,015 --> 00:06:02,225
You're the only one who'd know!

67
00:06:02,309 --> 00:06:04,477
Who is he? Is it…

68
00:06:07,480 --> 00:06:09,065
Is it serious?

69
00:06:09,816 --> 00:06:11,985
Ask her yourself.

70
00:06:12,068 --> 00:06:14,946
I don't care who she dates.

71
00:06:15,030 --> 00:06:16,406
This is so annoying.

72
00:06:16,948 --> 00:06:18,992
What? Did you two fight?

73
00:06:21,161 --> 00:06:24,497
Right. You didn't know about
Sol leaving as an exchange student too.

74
00:06:24,998 --> 00:06:28,084
We didn't fight. That's just
the extent of our relationship.

75
00:06:29,085 --> 00:06:30,128
I'm going.

76
00:06:44,142 --> 00:06:45,268
Seo Ji-wan.

77
00:06:46,102 --> 00:06:48,813
Ji-wan. Ji-wan!

78
00:06:49,689 --> 00:06:51,107
Let me talk to you.

79
00:06:53,985 --> 00:06:56,488
Fine. Talk.
What do you want to talk about first?

80
00:06:56,571 --> 00:06:59,366
Going abroad? Or your boyfriend?

81
00:07:00,116 --> 00:07:01,660
Everyone knew except me.

82
00:07:01,743 --> 00:07:03,370
I was going to tell you.

83
00:07:03,453 --> 00:07:05,872
Right. When were you going to tell me?

84
00:07:05,956 --> 00:07:08,625
The day before you left?
The day before you got married?

85
00:07:08,708 --> 00:07:11,503
What's with you?
You said you don't care who I date.

86
00:07:11,586 --> 00:07:13,088
Right. I don't.

87
00:07:13,171 --> 00:07:15,757
I'm just angry because
you're leaving me out like this.

88
00:07:15,840 --> 00:07:18,760
-When did I leave you out--
-You've always done this.

89
00:07:18,843 --> 00:07:22,597
You never tell me important things
about yourself. You know that?

90
00:07:24,933 --> 00:07:26,059
Like what?

91
00:07:39,614 --> 00:07:43,159
I guess this really is the extent
of our relationship.

92
00:08:08,184 --> 00:08:09,436
Thanks.

93
00:08:11,312 --> 00:08:12,647
What's your next class?

94
00:08:13,565 --> 00:08:16,234
Human Anatomy. It's so hard.

95
00:08:17,235 --> 00:08:18,903
I got an A in that class.

96
00:08:18,987 --> 00:08:20,321
-Really?
-Yes.

97
00:08:20,405 --> 00:08:23,283
-Then help me study.
-What will you do for me, then?

98
00:08:28,038 --> 00:08:29,456
What should I do for you?

99
00:08:31,791 --> 00:08:32,959
Jeez…

100
00:08:36,963 --> 00:08:39,924
By the way…

101
00:08:41,885 --> 00:08:43,011
Well…

102
00:08:44,137 --> 00:08:48,349
I don't want anyone to know about us.

103
00:08:50,685 --> 00:08:52,520
All right.

104
00:08:53,980 --> 00:08:55,190
-Okay.
-Okay.

105
00:08:56,524 --> 00:08:58,318
And…

106
00:08:59,152 --> 00:09:00,528
Well…

107
00:09:01,112 --> 00:09:02,447
You don't…

108
00:09:04,282 --> 00:09:08,495
have any diseases or anything, do you?

109
00:09:11,831 --> 00:09:12,791
Do you?

110
00:09:15,960 --> 00:09:18,213
Don't laugh! I'm serious.

111
00:09:19,589 --> 00:09:21,508
I don't, so don't worry.

112
00:09:23,885 --> 00:09:25,136
Okay.

113
00:09:26,679 --> 00:09:28,264
Do you have time later?

114
00:09:30,266 --> 00:09:32,894
Yes, I have some time.

115
00:09:32,977 --> 00:09:35,396
No, should we meet on Saturday?

116
00:09:36,898 --> 00:09:38,691
You need to rest the next day, right?

117
00:09:40,360 --> 00:09:43,780
No. It's totally fine.

118
00:10:18,022 --> 00:10:21,317
<i>Why did I do that? I acted so impulsively.</i>

119
00:10:22,986 --> 00:10:24,487
I must've lost my mind.

120
00:10:30,118 --> 00:10:32,245
I should just tell him not to come.

121
00:10:48,761 --> 00:10:50,680
-Come in.
-Hey.

122
00:10:57,353 --> 00:10:58,605
What's with the alcohol?

123
00:11:00,023 --> 00:11:01,941
It'll be nice to drink together.

124
00:11:02,025 --> 00:11:03,318
It'll be fun.

125
00:11:04,444 --> 00:11:06,738
Oh, I drank some already.

126
00:11:06,821 --> 00:11:09,490
<i>I couldn't do this sober.</i>

127
00:11:11,159 --> 00:11:12,827
This is cheating.

128
00:11:13,411 --> 00:11:14,287
What do you mean?

129
00:11:15,830 --> 00:11:18,041
We didn't decide on anything.

130
00:11:19,667 --> 00:11:21,210
Decide what?

131
00:11:21,294 --> 00:11:24,756
Weren't we going to study
Human Anatomy together?

132
00:11:26,341 --> 00:11:27,926
Oh, right.

133
00:11:29,302 --> 00:11:30,845
Right. Human Anatomy.

134
00:11:33,097 --> 00:11:35,016
Yes. We should study.

135
00:11:40,605 --> 00:11:42,023
Stop laughing.

136
00:11:44,233 --> 00:11:45,318
I have a gift for you.

137
00:11:55,578 --> 00:11:58,331
<i>Jae-eon is too smooth with everything.</i>

138
00:11:58,831 --> 00:12:02,627
<i>It's like everything
comes naturally to him.</i>

139
00:12:03,211 --> 00:12:04,712
All done.

140
00:12:08,841 --> 00:12:09,801
Do you like it?

141
00:12:11,386 --> 00:12:12,512
Yes.

142
00:12:14,764 --> 00:12:15,974
It's pretty.

143
00:12:16,599 --> 00:12:20,228
It'll be prettier
with the sunlight in the morning.

144
00:12:33,366 --> 00:12:35,535
<i>Like this was always
going to happen between us.</i>

145
00:12:40,873 --> 00:12:42,458
You got me again.

146
00:12:48,548 --> 00:12:49,757
Hang on.

147
00:12:54,971 --> 00:12:56,556
PARK JAE-EON

148
00:12:59,183 --> 00:13:00,560
You saved my number.

149
00:13:07,191 --> 00:13:08,860
<i>I can stop this right now.</i>

150
00:13:10,695 --> 00:13:14,657
<i>Because there are so many reasons
why I shouldn't do this.</i>

151
00:13:19,328 --> 00:13:20,621
<i>But…</i>

152
00:13:44,520 --> 00:13:46,230
You know, you have a mole here.

153
00:13:47,273 --> 00:13:48,107
Where?

154
00:13:49,108 --> 00:13:50,109
Here.

155
00:13:53,946 --> 00:13:55,156
I didn't know.

156
00:14:00,036 --> 00:14:02,997
You look even more pretty today.

157
00:14:03,081 --> 00:14:05,875
<i>I'm still attracted to him,
even at this moment.</i>

158
00:14:07,919 --> 00:14:09,420
<i>Like crazy.</i>

159
00:14:30,733 --> 00:14:32,610
<i>That one simple reason</i>

160
00:14:34,028 --> 00:14:36,489
<i>buries all my concerns again.</i>

161
00:14:42,120 --> 00:14:45,706
Didn't it hurt when you got that tattoo
behind your neck?

162
00:14:48,793 --> 00:14:50,420
Of course, it hurt.

163
00:14:51,587 --> 00:14:53,214
I almost died.

164
00:14:55,174 --> 00:14:56,843
I thought of quitting in the middle.

165
00:15:01,264 --> 00:15:03,057
I'm going to get another one soon.

166
00:15:04,225 --> 00:15:05,351
Where?

167
00:15:09,689 --> 00:15:11,065
Around here.

168
00:15:13,860 --> 00:15:15,445
Another butterfly?

169
00:15:15,528 --> 00:15:16,571
Yes.

170
00:15:18,239 --> 00:15:21,909
A butterfly with lots of black spots
on its wings.

171
00:15:21,993 --> 00:15:23,369
The name's pretty difficult.

172
00:15:24,078 --> 00:15:27,623
Taiwanese black-star hairstreak butterfly.

173
00:15:30,042 --> 00:15:31,169
Taiwan…

174
00:15:32,378 --> 00:15:33,838
That's a really long name.

175
00:15:37,675 --> 00:15:40,011
They eat flowers instead of leaves

176
00:15:40,094 --> 00:15:42,638
when they're caterpillars.

177
00:15:43,764 --> 00:15:45,057
It's unique, right?

178
00:15:46,934 --> 00:15:47,935
Yes.

179
00:15:48,936 --> 00:15:52,315
<i>Since that day, a lot of things
have changed between us.</i>

180
00:15:53,107 --> 00:15:56,360
<i>And Jae-eon slowly seeped into my life.</i>

181
00:16:01,741 --> 00:16:03,117
Get washed.

182
00:16:11,876 --> 00:16:13,878
I'm starting work
at the department office.

183
00:16:13,961 --> 00:16:16,881
You decided to do that? Aren't you busy?

184
00:16:16,964 --> 00:16:19,926
I won't work that long. Just for a while.

185
00:16:23,387 --> 00:16:24,514
It's because of you.

186
00:16:27,892 --> 00:16:28,935
Why?

187
00:16:30,895 --> 00:16:32,230
Come visit often.

188
00:16:33,356 --> 00:16:35,399
-Why would I?
-What?

189
00:16:37,193 --> 00:16:38,569
Come visit me.

190
00:16:40,321 --> 00:16:42,031
All right?

191
00:16:42,114 --> 00:16:43,241
Why would I?

192
00:16:45,493 --> 00:16:46,994
Okay, I will.

193
00:16:53,459 --> 00:16:56,879
Jae-eon, where's that suncatcher
you made last time?

194
00:16:56,963 --> 00:16:58,381
The butterfly-shaped one.

195
00:16:58,881 --> 00:17:00,049
Oh, that?

196
00:17:01,259 --> 00:17:02,510
I gifted it to someone.

197
00:17:02,593 --> 00:17:06,055
That's too bad. I wanted to see it
when it was finished.

198
00:17:06,138 --> 00:17:09,058
-Can you tell us how to make it?
-Tell us!

199
00:17:09,141 --> 00:17:11,394
Learn that from
the Ceramics and Glass students.

200
00:17:11,477 --> 00:17:13,437
Jae-eon is mine now.

201
00:17:14,814 --> 00:17:16,607
What are you talking about?

202
00:17:16,691 --> 00:17:18,693
Darn it! You're so noisy.

203
00:17:19,443 --> 00:17:22,738
If you're done, please just leave.

204
00:17:23,489 --> 00:17:26,075
-Guys, get out.
-Okay.

205
00:17:26,158 --> 00:17:28,160
-Bye.
-Bye.

206
00:17:31,205 --> 00:17:34,333
I heard he doesn't date,
but I guess he has a girlfriend.

207
00:17:34,417 --> 00:17:36,711
I wonder who it is.
She must be really pretty.

208
00:17:53,853 --> 00:17:55,896
-It's raining a lot.
-It is.

209
00:18:05,281 --> 00:18:07,742
-Don't do it.
-I have to do this!

210
00:18:07,825 --> 00:18:10,077
Stop working. Let's just sleep.

211
00:18:10,620 --> 00:18:11,954
-Already?
-Yes.

212
00:18:13,539 --> 00:18:15,916
-Already?
-Yes. I'm sleepy.

213
00:18:24,425 --> 00:18:28,679
<i>Our relationship only exists
at night, but…</i>

214
00:18:30,222 --> 00:18:31,932
Are you washing the dishes?

215
00:18:32,016 --> 00:18:35,186
Yes. It seems like you don't do the dishes
when I'm coming.

216
00:18:36,020 --> 00:18:37,021
You caught me.

217
00:18:37,688 --> 00:18:39,899
I think you're pretty good at housework.

218
00:18:40,775 --> 00:18:42,485
Will you do the laundry too?

219
00:18:43,277 --> 00:18:45,237
-Should I?
-Yes.

220
00:18:45,321 --> 00:18:49,408
-Then let's do it together.
-No. I don't want to do it.

221
00:18:49,492 --> 00:18:53,079
<i>It sometimes felt like we were lovers.</i>

222
00:18:53,788 --> 00:18:55,373
What's your goal today?

223
00:18:57,583 --> 00:19:00,503
Really? Can you do it?

224
00:19:02,588 --> 00:19:04,048
Don't strain yourself.

225
00:19:10,054 --> 00:19:11,055
What was that?

226
00:19:13,265 --> 00:19:16,602
My tongue gets numb when I eat this.

227
00:19:17,395 --> 00:19:18,604
So I kissed you first.

228
00:19:18,688 --> 00:19:21,774
<i>Jae-eon is still a mystery to me.</i>

229
00:19:21,857 --> 00:19:23,234
What are you on about?

230
00:19:23,317 --> 00:19:24,527
-Let's eat.
-Okay.

231
00:19:26,195 --> 00:19:27,363
Here.

232
00:19:31,659 --> 00:19:35,329
You said your tongue gets numb.
This is good, though.

233
00:19:35,830 --> 00:19:36,956
-Really?
-Yes.

234
00:19:43,170 --> 00:19:44,255
Just eat.

235
00:19:49,510 --> 00:19:51,679
-It's good, right?
-Yes. It's tastier today.

236
00:20:13,826 --> 00:20:17,079
<i>I can't tell if he's warm or cold,</i>

237
00:20:17,955 --> 00:20:20,499
<i>serious or joking.</i>

238
00:20:35,306 --> 00:20:37,099
Are you done with assignments?

239
00:20:37,725 --> 00:20:38,934
No.

240
00:20:40,060 --> 00:20:41,687
Go sleep at your house.

241
00:20:45,191 --> 00:20:46,817
I can't just leave.

242
00:21:00,414 --> 00:21:03,334
<i>My anxiety about Jae-eon
hasn't disappeared, but…</i>

243
00:21:14,470 --> 00:21:16,555
<i>We're much more compatible than I thought.</i>

244
00:21:22,561 --> 00:21:24,605
So the transverse arch

245
00:21:24,688 --> 00:21:26,690
can be seen the best from the front.

246
00:21:26,774 --> 00:21:29,902
I see. You're right.

247
00:21:30,778 --> 00:21:33,489
This is the transverse arch?

248
00:21:34,073 --> 00:21:35,032
Yes.

249
00:21:35,783 --> 00:21:38,452
And this is the medial longitudinal arch.

250
00:21:39,495 --> 00:21:42,331
-Yes.
-This is the lateral longitudinal arch.

251
00:21:43,374 --> 00:21:44,291
Correct.

252
00:21:46,877 --> 00:21:49,380
-What about this?
-Stop. It tickles.

253
00:21:49,463 --> 00:21:50,673
Stop.

254
00:21:50,756 --> 00:21:52,675
I'm studying right now.

255
00:21:54,051 --> 00:21:55,094
What about this?

256
00:21:55,177 --> 00:21:57,137
Hey, it tickles.

257
00:22:04,812 --> 00:22:06,772
<i>And I enjoy</i>

258
00:22:07,773 --> 00:22:09,233
<i>spending nights with him.</i>

259
00:22:18,158 --> 00:22:19,451
Thank you.

260
00:22:22,371 --> 00:22:23,872
-It looks delicious.
-I want corn.

261
00:22:23,956 --> 00:22:25,291
I thought you were on a diet.

262
00:22:25,374 --> 00:22:28,627
-That's why I'm only eating the shrimp.
-Oh, is that right?

263
00:22:31,880 --> 00:22:34,425
Are you dating someone these days?

264
00:22:35,009 --> 00:22:36,051
Me?

265
00:22:38,721 --> 00:22:40,264
No. Why?

266
00:22:40,347 --> 00:22:44,143
You just seem to be in a good mood
these days.

267
