happiness so I can feel proud?

526
00:43:32,932 --> 00:43:36,018
All right. Thank you!

527
00:43:36,102 --> 00:43:37,436
Wear it tomorrow, okay?

528
00:43:38,146 --> 00:43:39,355
Okay.

529
00:43:40,314 --> 00:43:43,568
But weren't you going to the exhibit?
It's the last day today.

530
00:43:45,361 --> 00:43:47,780
How could I think about that right now?

531
00:43:48,322 --> 00:43:50,199
<i>He's making me get my hopes up again.</i>

532
00:43:50,283 --> 00:43:51,284
Then…

533
00:43:52,285 --> 00:43:55,329
You got me a gift,
so let me buy you a meal.

534
00:43:55,955 --> 00:43:57,331
Well…

535
00:43:59,250 --> 00:44:00,877
Oh, do you have plans?

536
00:44:01,544 --> 00:44:02,628
Then--

537
00:44:02,712 --> 00:44:04,881
No. It's your birthday, so…

538
00:44:07,049 --> 00:44:09,051
INSTANT SEAWEED SOUP

539
00:44:13,306 --> 00:44:15,516
<i>I thought it was the worst birthday ever.</i>

540
00:44:16,392 --> 00:44:19,353
<i>But I guess life is full of variables.</i>

541
00:44:21,022 --> 00:44:22,982
Hang on. I'll make this right away.

542
00:44:27,904 --> 00:44:29,864
You're talking
as if you're really cooking.

543
00:44:31,073 --> 00:44:32,783
It's the heart that matters.

544
00:44:34,201 --> 00:44:37,496
It's been a while since I had
seaweed soup for my birthday.

545
00:44:39,832 --> 00:44:41,208
Really?

546
00:44:41,918 --> 00:44:44,587
I thought everyone had it except for me.

547
00:44:45,379 --> 00:44:46,547
I feel comforted now.

548
00:44:57,767 --> 00:44:58,768
What?

549
00:44:58,851 --> 00:45:01,020
You've never told me
something like that before.

550
00:45:02,730 --> 00:45:04,482
You don't talk much about yourself.

551
00:45:06,067 --> 00:45:07,401
Well…

552
00:45:11,989 --> 00:45:15,576
That's because
you know me so well already.

553
00:45:18,955 --> 00:45:20,706
I don't know anything about you.

554
00:45:27,421 --> 00:45:28,589
I really don't.

555
00:45:29,715 --> 00:45:31,509
You're still such a mystery to me.

556
00:45:39,976 --> 00:45:42,645
Stop fooling around
and finish making this.

557
00:45:43,229 --> 00:45:44,438
Not that.

558
00:45:46,941 --> 00:45:48,150
Then what?

559
00:46:51,714 --> 00:46:55,217
<i>Why can't you be my boyfriend?</i>

560
00:46:59,180 --> 00:47:01,807
So when are you going to make me
the seaweed soup?

561
00:47:04,185 --> 00:47:05,519
I'll make it now.

562
00:47:06,353 --> 00:47:08,105
Why aren't you getting up, then?

563
00:47:08,898 --> 00:47:11,067
I have no energy. Five more minutes.

564
00:47:24,538 --> 00:47:26,332
SEOL-A

565
00:47:29,543 --> 00:47:30,503
Let me take a call.

566
00:47:31,796 --> 00:47:33,089
Hang on.

567
00:47:38,177 --> 00:47:40,346
Should we have a drink first?

568
00:47:40,429 --> 00:47:43,015
Or go right away?

569
00:47:43,099 --> 00:47:45,518
Well, whatever you prefer.

570
00:47:51,774 --> 00:47:53,526
Let's drink here.

571
00:47:58,322 --> 00:47:59,698
What's your ideal type?

572
00:47:59,782 --> 00:48:00,991
-Me?
-Yes.

573
00:48:05,287 --> 00:48:06,247
Are you okay?

574
00:48:08,707 --> 00:48:10,292
Yes. I'm okay.

575
00:48:19,093 --> 00:48:23,013
This place is actually pretty lame.

576
00:48:26,100 --> 00:48:27,726
-Let's drink somewhere else.
-What?

577
00:48:27,810 --> 00:48:29,854
-Let's go.
-Somewhere else?

578
00:48:41,323 --> 00:48:42,908
Do you know her?

579
00:48:43,534 --> 00:48:45,202
No, I don't.

580
00:48:45,286 --> 00:48:47,621
Excuse me. Can I have some ice water?

581
00:48:51,959 --> 00:48:54,837
Sorry. Something urgent came up
with a friend.

582
00:48:56,714 --> 00:48:58,632
Okay. You should go, then.

583
00:48:59,216 --> 00:49:03,262
Make sure to eat.
And don't ignore your mom.

584
00:49:05,848 --> 00:49:07,016
I'll get going.

585
00:49:08,058 --> 00:49:09,226
Okay.

586
00:49:40,382 --> 00:49:41,842
I'm hungry.

587
00:50:40,359 --> 00:50:41,777
Do-hyeok…

588
00:50:50,119 --> 00:50:51,495
Come in.

589
00:50:57,126 --> 00:50:59,211
Sorry. You're closed, right? I…

590
00:50:59,295 --> 00:51:00,421
We're not.

591
00:51:07,594 --> 00:51:10,806
What? You have 3,000 subscribers?

592
00:51:11,390 --> 00:51:12,933
You started only three months ago.

593
00:51:13,017 --> 00:51:14,643
You have so many views.

594
00:51:14,727 --> 00:51:16,687
Do you edit the videos yourself?

595
00:51:17,438 --> 00:51:18,647
Yes.

596
00:51:20,524 --> 00:51:22,234
GRANDSON OF A NOODLE SHOP OWNER

597
00:51:22,318 --> 00:51:24,570
I saw this before.

598
00:51:25,446 --> 00:51:28,032
The channel name reminded me of you.

599
00:51:28,115 --> 00:51:29,616
You thought about me?

600
00:51:30,200 --> 00:51:31,452
Of course.

601
00:51:33,329 --> 00:51:35,789
I can't believe it really was you.

602
00:51:35,873 --> 00:51:37,333
And a culinary arts major?

603
00:51:38,500 --> 00:51:42,129
The Yang Do-hyeok I know

604
00:51:42,212 --> 00:51:44,923
always played with food.

605
00:51:48,844 --> 00:51:50,512
I knew you'd major in art, though.

606
00:51:51,430 --> 00:51:53,349
You were always good at drawing.

607
00:51:55,642 --> 00:51:57,019
Well…

608
00:51:58,979 --> 00:52:00,189
Not that good.

609
00:52:00,731 --> 00:52:02,483
I just liked it.

610
00:52:06,653 --> 00:52:08,572
Your videos are really good.

611
00:52:12,743 --> 00:52:13,744
Here you go.

612
00:52:18,832 --> 00:52:21,168
Weren't you making noodles for me?

613
00:52:21,794 --> 00:52:22,878
Next time.

614
00:52:23,629 --> 00:52:25,756
Isn't it your birthday today?

615
00:52:27,007 --> 00:52:28,467
You're right.

616
00:52:32,262 --> 00:52:34,932
You have a good memory.
You remembered my birthday?

617
00:52:35,557 --> 00:52:36,642
Of course, I…

618
00:52:40,521 --> 00:52:42,606
I have a good memory.

619
00:52:43,190 --> 00:52:44,108
Right.

620
00:52:44,775 --> 00:52:47,027
-Do you still like chocolate?
-Yes.

621
00:52:49,530 --> 00:52:51,240
Did you make this yourself, too?

622
00:52:52,032 --> 00:52:54,076
-Yes.
-You're so skilled.

623
00:52:54,159 --> 00:52:55,411
It looks delicious.

624
00:53:00,499 --> 00:53:01,500
What?

625
00:53:03,961 --> 00:53:05,170
Make a wish.

626
00:53:06,296 --> 00:53:07,673
A wish?

627
00:53:08,590 --> 00:53:09,842
All right.

628
00:53:29,194 --> 00:53:30,279
Happy birthday, Na-bi.

629
00:53:31,280 --> 00:53:34,491
Thank you. I can't believe
I'm with you like this on my birthday.

630
00:53:34,575 --> 00:53:36,493
Life is full of surprises.

631
00:53:37,077 --> 00:53:39,997
I know.
I never imagined this would happen.

632
00:53:42,833 --> 00:53:44,460
-It's so good.
-Really?

633
00:53:44,543 --> 00:53:46,128
-Yes!
-That's a relief.

634
00:53:46,712 --> 00:53:48,630
I felt this last time,

635
00:53:48,714 --> 00:53:51,508
but it's not awkward
even when we haven't met for a long time.

636
00:53:52,009 --> 00:53:54,261
Maybe since we're childhood friends.

637
00:53:54,344 --> 00:53:55,637
Do you think so?

638
00:53:55,721 --> 00:53:58,015
What's that response? Do you feel awkward?

639
00:53:59,433 --> 00:54:01,727
I feel kind of nervous.

640
00:54:07,774 --> 00:54:11,320
Remember when we had a birthday party
at the beach?

641
00:54:11,403 --> 00:54:12,654
Yes. Right.

642
00:54:13,947 --> 00:54:14,948
Of course I remember.

643
00:54:15,699 --> 00:54:18,410
We set up a tent and made <i>ramyeon</i>.

644
00:54:18,494 --> 00:54:21,121
Right. And we played with fireworks.

645
00:54:21,872 --> 00:54:23,123
Right.

646
00:54:23,207 --> 00:54:24,917
It was so fun.

647
00:54:26,835 --> 00:54:28,378
I want to go back to that moment.

648
00:55:07,501 --> 00:55:08,752
Do you like your gift?

649
00:55:10,379 --> 00:55:13,006
I've never been forced to receive
a gift like this.

650
00:55:13,590 --> 00:55:15,133
Wear it tomorrow, okay?

651
00:55:43,870 --> 00:55:45,998
-Hello?
-<i>Are you at school?</i>

652
00:55:46,081 --> 00:55:46,999
Yes. Why?

653
00:55:47,082 --> 00:55:50,002
I'm on my way. I'll be there soon.

654
00:55:50,836 --> 00:55:52,254
Me too.

655
00:56:09,229 --> 00:56:10,606
It looks good on you.

656
00:56:14,484 --> 00:56:16,278
Because you bought it?

657
00:56:16,361 --> 00:56:18,864
Well, the model is pretty.

658
00:56:21,325 --> 00:56:22,409
You're right.

659
00:56:24,578 --> 00:56:26,413
Right, I made up with my mom.

660
00:56:26,496 --> 00:56:28,457
Well, it was more like

661
00:56:28,540 --> 00:56:30,834
I just listened to her talk and hung up.

662
00:56:32,586 --> 00:56:33,795
Good job.

663
00:56:36,256 --> 00:56:39,259
What about you?
You went to see your friend.

664
00:56:40,844 --> 00:56:41,720
Right.

665
00:56:43,555 --> 00:56:44,681
It wasn't anything good.

666
00:56:45,849 --> 00:56:48,518
<i>He's drawing the line again.</i>

667
00:56:53,899 --> 00:56:55,442
Why aren't you giving me one?

668
00:56:56,485 --> 00:56:58,195
What flavor is it?

669
00:57:10,290 --> 00:57:12,417
Are you crazy? We're at school!

670
00:57:13,877 --> 00:57:16,630
A pretty girl was gazing at me, asking me

671
00:57:17,547 --> 00:57:19,007
the flavor of my candy.

672
00:57:25,180 --> 00:57:27,391
I was only looking at your candy.

673
00:57:30,560 --> 00:57:32,270
-This?
-Yes, that.

674
00:57:35,065 --> 00:57:36,108
It tastes good, right?

675
00:57:37,275 --> 00:57:38,819
-Is it good?
-No.

676
00:57:38,902 --> 00:57:40,445
-It's not?
-No.

677
00:57:41,488 --> 00:57:44,574
There's something between them.
And my friend said

678
00:57:44,658 --> 00:57:48,203
she saw Jae-eon several times at the
convenience store near Na-bi's house.

679
00:57:48,286 --> 00:57:50,872
Come on. She lives near our school.

680
00:57:50,956 --> 00:57:52,916
He never goes to that convenience store.

681
00:57:53,959 --> 00:57:56,461
You know so much about Jae-eon, honey.

682
00:57:56,545 --> 00:57:58,088
Did you just call me "honey"?

683
00:57:58,171 --> 00:58:00,048
Come to think of it,

684
00:58:00,132 --> 00:58:02,843
they were giving each other looks
before they disappeared!

685
00:58:02,926 --> 00:58:04,636
Are they dating, then?

686
00:58:05,721 --> 00:58:07,472
Jae-eon doesn't date.

687
00:58:07,556 --> 00:58:09,683
Then are they just sleeping
with each other?

688
00:58:09,766 --> 00:58:11,977
You can gossip among yourselves later.

689
00:58:13,020 --> 00:58:15,814
We still have to discuss the venue
and budget of our workshop.

690
00:58:15,897 --> 00:58:18,150
Didn't we decide to finish this
in an hour?

691
00:58:18,233 --> 00:58:20,736
Come on, don't be so serious.

692
00:58:20,819 --> 00:58:22,195
It's all right.

693
00:58:22,279 --> 00:58:24,489
I guess he's in a hurry to go on a date.

694
00:58:25,115 --> 00:58:26,658
Let's finish up quickly.

695
00:58:31,121 --> 00:58:33,373
-Sorry I'm late.
-It's fine. Sit down.

696
00:58:35,083 --> 00:58:38,128
The professor wants us to check
the venue in person beforehand.

697
00:58:38,211 --> 00:58:40,130
We should go this weekend.

698
00:58:40,714 --> 00:58:42,466
Who can't make it?

699
00:58:47,179 --> 00:58:49,765
What? You can't make it, Jae-eon?

700
00:58:50,682 --> 00:58:51,767
No.

701
00:58:53,602 --> 00:58:54,644
Why?

702
00:59:01,151 --> 00:59:02,569
Hey, Na-bi!

703
00:59:03,111 --> 00:59:05,447
Why are you so dressed up today?

704
00:59:05,530 --> 00:59:07,491
-Is it okay?
-It looks great on you.

705
00:59:10,911 --> 00:59:12,370
Why weren't you at school?

706
00:59:12,454 --> 00:59:15,290
I was a little sick.
Don't you think I lost some weight?

707
00:59:15,874 --> 00:59:18,043
Yes, it looks like it. Are you okay now?

708
00:59:18,126 --> 00:59:20,921
I'm fine.
Right, and how was your birthday?

709
00:59:21,004 --> 00:59:22,547
Sorry I couldn't contact you.

710
00:59:22,631 --> 00:59:24,216
You don't need to be sorry.

711
00:59:24,758 --> 00:59:28,053
Did you talk to Sol?
She seemed pretty worried about you.

712
00:59:28,970 --> 00:59:32,140
The weather's really nice today.

713
00:59:32,724 --> 00:59:35,352
-It's totally spring, isn't it?
-It is.

714
00:59:37,187 --> 00:59:39,147
I don't want to work on assignments.

715
00:59:39,231 --> 00:59:41,608
Hey, Na-bi. You look so pretty.

716
00:59:41,691 --> 00:59:42,984
-Here to work?
-So pretty.

717
00:59:43,068 --> 00:59:45,612
-We're just having a short meeting.
-They're both pretty.

718
00:59:47,656 --> 00:59:48,740
Okay.

719
00:59:50,617 --> 00:59:51,660
Go on.

720
01:00:02,671 --> 01:00:04,714
What about me?

721
01:00:04,798 --> 01:00:06,424
It's been a while, Ji-wan.

722
01:00:06,508 --> 01:00:08,552
Why did you suddenly go off the grid?

723
01:00:08,635 --> 01:00:10,220
I was a bit sick.

724
01:00:12,430 --> 01:00:15,100
How does a fit girl like you
suddenly get sick?

725
01:00:15,684 --> 01:00:17,144
I know. Ji-wan is built like a brick.

726
01:00:17,227 --> 01:00:18,895
What were you sick with?

727
01:00:19,771 --> 01:00:23,066
Well, Jae-eon can't come
since he has plans.

728
01:00:23,150 --> 01:00:24,651
Anyone else who can't come?

729
01:00:25,694 --> 01:00:29,489
Na-bi. We're going to check the venue
for our workshop. Want to come?

730
01:00:30,407 --> 01:00:31,616
Well…

731
01:00:36,538 --> 01:00:38,415
I have plans.

732
01:00:39,332 --> 01:00:42,586
Right. If you have plans, I guess not.

733
01:00:59,269 --> 01:01:02,230
Na-bi and Jae-eon really seem
to be dating, right?

734
01:01:02,731 --> 01:01:04,774
I thought Na-bi had a crush on me.

735
01:01:05,483 --> 01:01:08,236
Are you still on about that?

736
01:01:09,237 --> 01:01:11,448
Do you guys want to go out for drinks?

737
01:01:11,531 --> 01:01:12,991
I have plans.

738
01:01:14,701 --> 01:01:16,620
Me too. I have plans, too.

739
01:01:29,257 --> 01:01:31,801
Jeez…

740
01:01:40,352 --> 01:01:41,478
What are you doing here?

741
01:01:41,561 --> 01:01:44,356
Na-bi. I'm really heartbroken.

742
01:01:44,439 --> 01:01:46,191
I know you're in a lot of pain after--

743
01:01:46,274 --> 01:01:47,734
What are you talking about?

744
01:01:50,654 --> 01:01:53,740
I heard the rumors. A lot of my students
attend your school.

745
01:01:53,823 --> 01:01:56,785
I keep hearing rumors about you,
even if I try not to.

746
01:01:56,868 --> 01:01:58,036
What do you mean?

747
01:01:59,162 --> 01:02:01,456
-What rumors?
-I heard you're seeing

748
01:02:02,165 --> 01:02:04,459
some jerk named Park Jae-eon or something.

749
01:02:05,210 --> 01:02:07,212
I heard he sleeps with everybody.

750
01:02:07,295 --> 01:02:09,798
I was so shocked when I heard
you were seeing him.

751
01:02:14,678 --> 01:02:17,222
I don't enjoy hearing that about my ex.

752
01:02:19,683 --> 01:02:20,767
Let go of me.

753
01:02:21,810 --> 01:02:24,187
You're giving me advice?
Who do you think you are?

754
01:02:24,271 --> 01:02:27,107
What? Then it's true?
You're seeing that jerk?

755
01:02:27,190 --> 01:02:29,067
Who are you to call him a jerk?

756
01:02:29,150 --> 01:02:30,694
-Yu Na-bi!
-What?

757
01:02:34,072 --> 01:02:36,324
You're not that kind of girl.

758
01:02:36,408 --> 01:02:40,745
You must've been lonely after we broke up.
But still, seeing a guy like that?

759
01:02:40,829 --> 01:02:42,330
Shut up and get lost.

760
01:02:49,254 --> 01:02:50,714
Hey, Na-bi…

761
01:02:53,550 --> 01:02:56,845
LAUNDRY

762
01:03:08,106 --> 01:03:10,150
That bastard.
Who is he to say such things?

763
01:03:34,090 --> 01:03:36,551
<i>I feel like I'm doing something wrong.</i>

764
01:03:38,261 --> 01:03:40,096
Don't you know any hot girls?

765
01:03:40,805 --> 01:03:43,058
Ask Jae-eon to introduce you.

766
01:03:44,142 --> 01:03:45,018
Park Jae-eon?

767
01:03:45,810 --> 01:03:48,229
To be honest,
we don't feel comfortable with him.

768
01:03:48,980 --> 01:03:51,566
Why? Did something happen?

769
01:03:51,649 --> 01:03:54,778
Don't you feel that he shows off
about being popular?

770
01:03:54,861 --> 01:03:57,238
When I asked him to introduce me
to a girl,

771
01:03:57,322 --> 01:04:01,034
he said something about feeling guilty
towards them. It totally pissed me off.

772
01:04:01,618 --> 01:04:04,454
Jae-eon really said that to you?

773
01:04:04,537 --> 01:04:06,164
He did.

774
01:04:06,247 --> 01:04:08,083
He's so rude just because he's popular.

775
01:04:08,166 --> 01:04:10,043
We don't think of him as a real friend.

776
01:04:10,126 --> 01:04:12,295
The others don't consider him
a friend, either.

777
01:04:12,379 --> 01:04:15,298
They just keep him close
since he's good-looking, that's all.

778
01:04:16,966 --> 01:04:18,593
His target is Na-bi these days.

779
01:04:19,260 --> 01:04:20,845
They seem to be getting close.

780
01:04:20,929 --> 01:04:22,430
I could totally tell.

781
01:04:23,056 --> 01:04:24,849
I did hear about that.

782
01:04:25,517 --> 01:04:27,310
So the rumors spread already.

783
01:04:27,394 --> 01:04:29,354
Jae-eon has nothing to lose.

784
01:04:29,437 --> 01:04:30,563
He must be so proud.

785
01:04:31,731 --> 01:04:34,984
I didn't think Na-bi would be like that.
She must be pretty open-minded…

786
01:04:35,735 --> 01:04:39,406
Open-minded?
That's just a nice way to put it.

787
01:04:40,115 --> 01:04:43,451
You really can't judge a book
by its cover.

788
01:04:44,369 --> 01:04:46,162
I should get going now.

789
01:04:46,746 --> 01:04:48,248
Okay. Let's go together.

790
01:04:53,503 --> 01:04:54,712
Yu Na-bi?

791
01:04:58,258 --> 01:04:59,926
Hello, Professor.

792
01:05:02,846 --> 01:05:04,097
Is this for the exhibit?

793
01:05:05,432 --> 01:05:07,976
Yes, I'm thinking of handing this one in.

794
01:05:16,568 --> 01:05:18,194
Is something troubling you?

795
01:05:18,278 --> 01:05:19,696
It's in pretty bad shape.

796
01:05:20,405 --> 01:05:21,739
<i>A right hook.</i>

797
01:05:23,199 --> 01:05:27,162
But still, if you focus well
and keep working on it,

798
01:05:27,996 --> 01:05:29,456
it could be a decent piece.

799
01:05:29,539 --> 01:05:32,083
All right. I'll work harder.

800
01:05:47,974 --> 01:05:52,479
People gossip about others

801
01:05:52,562 --> 01:05:54,814
and criticize others so easily.

802
01:05:54,898 --> 01:05:57,859
It's especially worse in Korea,
since it's a small country.

803
01:05:59,152 --> 01:06:02,614
That's why you should be careful
when you're young.

804
01:06:03,615 --> 01:06:06,993
You might think reckless behavior
can be forgiven because you're young.

805
01:06:10,163 --> 01:06:12,790
But from what I experienced,
it's not the case.

806
01:06:13,374 --> 01:06:14,584
There are consequences.

807
01:06:14,667 --> 01:06:17,837
You'll get hit with the aftermath
at a crucial moment later on.

808
01:06:17,921 --> 01:06:19,380
<i>A left hook.</i>

809
01:06:19,464 --> 01:06:22,217
No one will take responsibility
for your own life.

810
01:06:22,300 --> 01:06:25,845
So keep your head on straight.
You're graduating soon, you know.

811
01:06:25,929 --> 01:06:28,348
Everyone finds a job
before they graduate these days.

812
01:06:28,973 --> 01:06:30,683
<i>And an uppercut.</i>

813
01:06:31,518 --> 01:06:32,602
Right.

814
01:06:33,436 --> 01:06:34,854
I know how you feel,

815
01:06:34,938 --> 01:06:38,066
so I'm giving you advice since
I care about you. So keep that in mind.

816
01:06:38,900 --> 01:06:40,235
Yes, Professor.

817
01:06:40,944 --> 01:06:43,863
-Focus on your work.
-I will.

818
01:06:50,745 --> 01:06:51,955
<i>KO.</i>

819
01:07:05,301 --> 01:07:06,803
<i>It feels like</i>

820
01:07:06,886 --> 01:07:10,348
<i>the whole universe is telling me
to end it with Jae-eon.</i>

821
01:07:11,182 --> 01:07:12,350
Na-bi.

822
01:07:14,894 --> 01:07:18,022
Are you okay? You could've
fallen down on the trash.

823
01:07:18,898 --> 01:07:21,109
Yes, I'm fine.

824
01:07:21,901 --> 01:07:24,070
This is good timing.

825
01:07:24,153 --> 01:07:27,156
Could we meet for a moment later?
Just the two of us?

826
01:07:29,242 --> 01:07:31,661
Well, I like that you're asking first,

827
01:07:32,370 --> 01:07:35,123
but I'll be a bit tired
since I have lots of work today.

828
01:07:36,666 --> 01:07:39,252
What? I'm not talking about that.

829
01:07:41,546 --> 01:07:43,631
Let's talk.

830
01:07:44,757 --> 01:07:47,552
Okay. Will it be okay
to meet late at night?

831
01:07:47,635 --> 01:07:48,761
Yes, it's fine.

832
01:07:50,054 --> 01:07:51,514
I'll call you when I'm done.

833
01:07:53,016 --> 01:07:54,017
Okay.

834
01:08:05,737 --> 01:08:08,448
-Let's send it to the professor tomorrow.
-Okay.

835
01:08:08,531 --> 01:08:10,408
She won't read it until tomorrow anyway.

836
01:08:19,042 --> 01:08:20,627
-Aren't you leaving?
-What?

837
01:08:21,169 --> 01:08:26,049
Oh, well… I'm just going to finish
reading the paper I was looking at.

838
01:08:28,009 --> 01:08:29,052
Where is it?

839
01:08:29,135 --> 01:08:31,679
All right, then. I'll be off first.

840
01:08:32,680 --> 01:08:34,182
Okay. Bye.

841
01:08:36,351 --> 01:08:40,188
I thought about it, and I guess
I must have lost it after breaking up.

842
01:08:40,271 --> 01:08:42,106
I don't know why I'm doing this

843
01:08:42,190 --> 01:08:44,108
with you.

844
01:08:47,445 --> 01:08:48,780
What do you mean?

845
01:08:51,366 --> 01:08:53,951
I want to focus on my work and school.

846
01:08:56,579 --> 01:08:58,456
This is an important time for me.

847
01:09:00,249 --> 01:09:02,168
I guess I'm talking too much, right?

848
01:09:02,877 --> 01:09:06,839
Yes. Aren't you going overboard?
We're not even going out.

849
01:09:11,344 --> 01:09:12,553
We should end it.

850
01:09:18,142 --> 01:09:20,353
Does this sound like I want to cut ties?

851
01:09:24,941 --> 01:09:27,568
But whatever I say,

852
01:09:27,652 --> 01:09:30,947
Jae-eon won't even blink an eye.

853
01:09:36,953 --> 01:09:40,790
<i>He's always so relaxed and calm,
but I'm always anxious.</i>

854
01:09:40,873 --> 01:09:44,335
<i>My ex cheated on me,
I got rejected by a guy who liked me,</i>

855
01:09:44,419 --> 01:09:46,963
<i>and rumors spread about me
being sex partners with the guy I like.</i>

856
01:09:49,549 --> 01:09:52,176
It sounds even worse like that.

857
01:10:01,018 --> 01:10:02,437
<i>We should end it.</i>

858
01:10:03,354 --> 01:10:04,939
<i>That's all I have to say.</i>

859
01:10:22,623 --> 01:10:23,916
Let's talk.

860
01:10:24,000 --> 01:10:25,626
You have more to say?

861
01:10:27,253 --> 01:10:30,465
To be honest, I don't get
why you're so upset.

862
01:10:32,341 --> 01:10:34,427
You didn't need to ghost me like that.

863
01:10:38,556 --> 01:10:40,308
I said I'll see you at your house.

864
01:10:42,059 --> 01:10:44,312
I thought you'd take a long time.

865
01:10:45,480 --> 01:10:48,900
I thought I'd finish by 10 p.m.,
but it's taking longer than expected.

866
01:10:49,525 --> 01:10:50,526
Right.

867
01:10:52,320 --> 01:10:53,446
I see.

868
01:10:53,529 --> 01:10:57,074
<i>I ran thousands of simulations
inside my head…</i>

869
01:10:58,159 --> 01:10:59,577
You look pretty serious.

870
01:11:02,163 --> 01:11:03,623
What did you want to say?

871
01:11:03,706 --> 01:11:06,000
<i>But the moment I looked into his eyes,</i>

872
01:11:07,543 --> 01:11:09,629
<i>my mind went blank.</i>

873
01:11:09,712 --> 01:11:11,005
Well…

874
01:11:13,591 --> 01:11:15,885
My ex-boyfriend came to my house.

875
01:11:15,968 --> 01:11:18,721
He seemed to have heard rumors about us.

876
01:11:20,932 --> 01:11:22,809
He said I should just date him instead.

877
01:11:25,853 --> 01:11:27,021
What did you say?

878
01:11:28,022 --> 01:11:29,774
I told him not to talk nonsense.

879
01:11:31,025 --> 01:11:32,026
Really?

880
01:11:32,109 --> 01:11:35,071
<i>"Really?" Is that it?</i>

881
01:11:40,159 --> 01:11:41,828
Is that what you wanted to say?

882
01:11:46,791 --> 01:11:49,126
Is there someone else you're seeing?

883
01:11:49,210 --> 01:11:50,628
<i>What's wrong with me?</i>

884
01:11:51,128 --> 01:11:53,673
<i>Why am I asking this
when I was about to end everything?</i>

885
01:11:58,803 --> 01:11:59,887
No.

886
01:12:01,305 --> 01:12:02,223
Really?

887
01:12:18,072 --> 01:12:19,532
Excuse me.

888
01:12:20,116 --> 01:12:22,743
Are you Park Jae-eon, by any chance?

889
01:12:23,870 --> 01:12:25,204
Yes.

890
01:12:26,873 --> 01:12:28,249
So it's you.

891
01:12:31,294 --> 01:12:33,087
You bastard!

892
01:12:35,006 --> 01:12:36,883
Sir! What's wrong?

893
01:12:36,966 --> 01:12:39,010
-What are you doing?
-Move.

894
01:12:39,093 --> 01:12:40,511
-Wait!
-Move!

895
01:12:40,595 --> 01:12:43,180
-Why are you doing this?
-Get out of the way!

896
01:12:45,266 --> 01:12:46,225
Na-bi!

897
01:13:41,697 --> 01:13:45,743
<i>Park Jae-eon has never been mine.
But it feels like I've lost him.</i>

898
01:13:45,826 --> 01:13:48,496
<i>How could Na-bi date a guy like Jae-eon?</i>

899
01:13:48,579 --> 01:13:52,166
-My girlfriend?
-Call me. Even if it's nothing special.

900
01:13:52,249 --> 01:13:55,211
<i>My whole house is filled
with traces of Jae-eon.</i>

901
01:13:55,294 --> 01:13:56,128
<i>Jerk.</i>

902
01:13:56,837 --> 01:13:58,339
<i>I guess it worked.</i>

903
01:13:58,422 --> 01:14:00,007
<i>How long are you going to avoid me?</i>

904
01:14:00,091 --> 01:14:01,884
We didn't get to finish
what we were talking about.

905
01:14:01,968 --> 01:14:05,721
This is how we always make up.
As if nothing happened.

906
01:14:05,805 --> 01:14:07,515
I just picked it up, thinking of you.

907
01:14:07,598 --> 01:14:09,558
-A gift for me?
-Yes.

908
01:14:09,642 --> 01:14:11,352
I was jealous.
Good luck on your presentation.

909
01:14:11,435 --> 01:14:13,854
<i>Who would like to assist Yu Na-bi?</i>

910
01:14:13,938 --> 01:14:16,023
I thought it'd be fun. Seems interesting.

911
01:14:16,107 --> 01:14:17,984
<i>Hey, Seol-a. I'll be there right away.</i>

912
01:14:18,067 --> 01:14:20,361
<i>How can he not even call once?</i>

913
01:14:20,444 --> 01:14:21,904
<i>I miss him.</i>

914
01:14:22,446 --> 01:14:26,575
Subtitle translation by: Ju-young Park
